William Woodruff
Professor John Beckett writes:
In his sequel to William Woodruff (25 September) stated that "in 1946 he resumed studies in economic history at Oxford and in 1950 he won a Houblon-Norman research fellowship... at the same time he was studying for a bachelor's degree, a master's degree and a doctoral degree."
